1
Test Operations Management 
Oversee daily test operations — from scheduling, setup, and execution to post-test reporting.
Manage both online and offline (center-based) testing environments, ensuring reliability and security.
Ensure adherence to all testing protocols, guidelines, and data integrity standards.
Supervise test delivery teams and ensure SLA compliance across all operational metrics.
Team Leadership & People Management 
Lead, mentor, and train a team of Test Operations Associates and Executives.
Create staffing plans for high-volume test seasons, ensuring adequate coverage.
Conduct performance reviews, set KPIs, and drive accountability across the team.
Process Improvement & Quality Assurance 
Develop and standardize SOPs (Standard Operating Procedures) for test operations.
Identify operational bottlenecks and drive continuous improvement initiatives.
Implement quality checks and feedback loops to minimize errors and downtime.
Collaborate with product and engineering teams to enhance testing platforms and workflows.
Data Analysis & Reporting 
Track and analyze test performance metrics (attendance rates, issue logs, completion rates, etc.).
Present actionable insights to leadership for process enhancement and resource optimization.
Build dashboards and reports for visibility into daily and monthly operational performance.
Stakeholder & Cross-Functional Collaboration 
Partner with Content, Product, Technology, Customer Support, and Business teams to ensure operational readiness.
Act as the primary point of contact for internal and external stakeholders related to testing operations.
Manage vendor relationships, including exam center partners and third-party service providers.
Risk & Incident Management 
Monitor test sessions in real time to detect and address irregularities or technical issues.
Ensure incident escalation protocols are followed, with root-cause analysis and preventive measures in place.
Maintain compliance with data security, integrity, and privacy requirements.
